# Deployment

I deployed Wazuh using the **official Wazuh Installation Assistant**.

The deployment automatically installed:

- Wazuh Manager
- Wazuh Dashboard
- Wazuh Indexer

Rather than reproducing the installation commands, please refer to the official Wazuh documentation linked above.

---

# Extract Installation Credentials

After installation completed successfully, I extracted the credentials generated by the installation assistant.

```bash
sudo tar -xvf wazuh-install-files.tar
```

These credentials were used to log into the Wazuh Dashboard.

---

# Verify the Wazuh Installation

To verify that Wazuh had been deployed correctly, I checked the installed version.

```bash
sudo /var/ossec/bin/wazuh-control info
```

Output:

```text
WAZUH_VERSION="v4.14.6"
WAZUH_REVISION="rc2"
WAZUH_TYPE="server"
```

This confirms that the Wazuh Manager was successfully deployed.

---

